  "text": "Septin filament formation was analyzed essentially as described previously [CITATION_1] . Purified septin complex was applied to nickel Formvar carbon-coated grids and incubated at room temperature for 4 min. Excess solution was removed from the grids and proteins were fixed with 1% uranyl acetate in 30% ethanol for 30 s. Fixative was removed, and grids were dried after which images were taken on a Philips FEI Tecnai Spirit transmission electron microscope at 60 kV.",
